The paper deals with the problem of preprocessing a string to efficiently answer queries about its shortest unique substrings. This problem involves data structures and algorithms for string processing, which are typically studied in the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial and structural analysis of the problem, which could fall under the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) sub-categories. The paper uses techniques from computational geometry, which could place it in the cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves probabilistic arguments and analysis, which could fall under the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
